<subSubSection id="C35E4AE42B6BFFD7FF7FFAF9DB01FA50" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFB196F2B6BFFD7FF7FFAF9DB01FA50" blockId="3.[151,1436,1352,1450]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis id="B930C57D2B6BFFD7FF7FFAF9DB0DFA98" bold="true" box="[199,334,1352,1378]" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name comes from the Latin adjective 
<taxonomicName id="4C4462EC2B6BFFD7FC34FAF8D9B0FA98" authorityName="Ng &amp; Kottelat" authorityYear="2022" box="[908,1011,1353,1378]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Siluridae" genus="Silurichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="188" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="exortivus">
<emphasis id="B930C57D2B6BFFD7FC34FAF8D9B0FA98" box="[908,1011,1353,1378]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="188">exortivus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning “towards the sunrise”. This name is used in allusion to distribution of this species (eastern Borneo), which represents the easternmost limit of its distribution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
